</div>

<div class="container">
  <!-- Quote -->
  <figure>
    <blockquote class="blockquote text-center mt-5">
        "The Tigris River may be thousands of miles away, but its spirit flows through every dish we serve."
    </blockquote>
  </figure>
  {{!-- Story --}}
  <div class="row featurette my-5">
    <div class="col-md-7 fs-5">
      <p>Welcome to Tigris Mediterranean Grille, where every dish
        is a voyage through the rich tapestry of time, history, and culture.
      </p>
      <p>Our story begins in 2000, in the heart of Baghdad, Iraq—a city
        where the Tigris River has flowed for millennia, nurturing
        civilizations and shaping cultures. It was here, along the banks of
        this ancient river, that we first opened our doors, inspired by the
        rich culinary traditions of Mesopotamia and a deep love for the flavors
        of our homeland.</p>
      <img src="/images/misc/tigris-river-5.jpg" style="height:500px" class="d-block w-100 mb-3" alt="Baghdad" loading="lazy">
      <p>
        Our vision was clear: to bring the authentic tastes of the Middle East to life,
        crafting each dish in an ambiance that exudes warmth, hospitality, and the depth of our culture.
      </p>
      <p>
        In 2003, as Baghdad entered a new chapter in its storied history, so
        did we. Amidst the challenges of a new era, we were honored to serve
        those who came from afar, including the US army and embassy. It was a
        time marked by both turmoil and hope, and through it all, our kitchen
        became a sanctuary—a place where the universal language
        of food transcended borders and brought people together. </p>
      <img src="/images/misc/amman-jordan-2.jpg" style="height:500px" class="d-block w-100 mb-3" alt="Amman" loading="lazy">
      <p>But our journey was far from over. In 2005, Tigris Mediterranean Grille
        expanded to Amman, Jordan. Nestled in the vibrant streets of Amman, we quickly
        became a beacon for those seeking the true tastes of Iraq and the broader Middle
        East, combined with a touch of modern elegance. Our commitment to innovation and
        authenticity resonated with locals and visitors alike.
        <p />
      <p>In 2012, we took another bold step, crossing oceans to open in San
        Diego, California. Here, we blended the rich flavors of our heritage
        with the diverse culinary landscape of the United States. While the
        Tigris River may be thousands of miles away, its spirit flows
        through every dish we serve, connecting our guests to the deep
        history and culture of Iraq.</p>
      <img src="/images/misc/raw-colored-1.png" style="height:500px" class="d-block w-100 mb-3" alt="Tigris" loading="lazy">
      <p>At Tigris Mediterranean Grille, every meal is more than just food—it's
        a story. A connection to a culture as rich and deep as the river that inspires us. We invite
        you to join us and experience the flavors, stories, and traditions that have shaped our journey.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-5">
      <img class="featurette-image img-fluid mx-auto rounded" src="/images/food/catering-1.jpg" alt="Food" loading="lazy">
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

